#: ../../../reference/markdown-for-agents.rst:2
msgid "Markdown for AI agents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/markdown-for-agents.rst:4
msgid ""
"Read the Docs serves a Markdown version of documentation pages to clients "
"that request it, using HTTP content negotiation. Markdown is smaller and "
"easier to parse than rendered HTML, which makes it a better format for AI "
"agents and language models to consume."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/markdown-for-agents.rst:9
msgid ""
"This feature is **enabled automatically** on all documentation domains "
"hosted on Read the Docs, with no configuration required. Browsers continue "
"to receive the regular HTML version of your documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/markdown-for-agents.rst:13
msgid "A request with ``Accept: text/markdown`` returns a Markdown response:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/markdown-for-agents.rst:15
msgid ""
"$ curl -i https://docs.readthedocs.com/platform/stable/ -H \"Accept: text/"
"markdown\"\n"
"HTTP/2 200\n"
"content-type: text/markdown; charset=utf-8\n"
"vary: accept\n"
"x-markdown-tokens: 1496\n"
"content-signal: ai-train=yes, search=yes, ai-input=yes\n"
"\n"
"---\n"
"description: Automate building, versioning, and hosting of your technical "
"documentation continuously on Read the Docs.\n"
"title: Read the Docs: documentation simplified\n"
"---\n"
"\n"
"..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/markdown-for-agents.rst:31
msgid ""
"This feature is powered by `Cloudflare`_. See the `Cloudflare blog post on "
"Markdown for agents`_ for more details about how the conversion works."
msgstr ""

